creator: Salt-N-Pepa
title: The C64: Are You Wasting Your Life… YET?
description:
In part an in-depth review of the "Commodore 64 Mini", this is not a "top ten" list, this is not a "hidden gems" list… this is an inevitable reflection on the meaning of life, given the stunning meaninglessness of the nostalgia for the video games of our childhood that so many of us are burdened with.
Credit for the music goes to a small channel called "Meme Music", give them some encouragement: https://www.youtube.com/c/MemeMusic/videos
The particular song quoted had fewer than 100 views when I found it: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ItMRSOJGQfQ
Support the creation of new content on the channel (and speak to me, directly, if you want to) via Patreon, for $1 per month: https://www.patreon.com/a_bas_le_ciel
Why are comments disabled on my youtube channel?  Here's the answer, in a relatively uplifting 5 minute video: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=EHb9k30KTXM
A searchable list of all of my videos (more effective than searching within youtube, IMO) can be found here: https://aryailia.github.io/a-bas-le-ciel/all.html
Find me on Instagram: https://www.instagram.com/a_bas_le_ciel/?hl=en
You may not know that I have several youtube channels, one of them is AR&IO (Active Research & Informed Opinion) found here: https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCP3fLeOekX2yBegj9-XwDhA/videos
Another is à-bas-le-ciel, found here: https://www.youtube.com/user/HeiJinZhengZhi/videos
And there is, in fact, a youtube channel that has my own legal name, Eisel Mazard: https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCuxp5G-XFGcH4lmgejZddqA/videos
#C64Mini #Commodore64 #C64Maxi
